Heat the oil in a large, lidded saucepan over a medium heat. Add the carrots and celery and season with salt and pepper to taste. Put the lid on and sweat for about 10 minutes, or until the vegetables have softened.Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute, then stir in the chopped tomatoes and stock. Simmer for 15 minutes with the lid on.Add the spaghetti and cook for 7â€“10 minutes, or until soft. Add the peas and beans and heat through.Serve with slices of baguette.